textAfterTable: 54598 Bienor           Discovered 2000 Aug. 27 by the Deep Ecliptic Survey. Bienor, one of the centaurs who tried to kidnap the bride Hippodame and other women at the wedding of Pirithous, was overcome by the hero Theseus, who jumped on his back, smashed his face and pounded his temples. The name was suggested by E. K. Elliot.
